How Gantt Charts Assist in Project Scheduling
A Gantt chart is a visual project management tool that displays tasks along a timeline. Each task is represented by a horizontal bar, showing its start and end date, dependencies, and progress.

ðŸ”¹ How Gantt Charts Improve Scheduling:
âœ… Clear Visual Representation â€“ Makes it easy to see task durations, dependencies, and project progress.
âœ… Task Dependencies & Sequencing â€“ Identifies which tasks must be completed before others can begin.
âœ… Milestone Tracking â€“ Highlights key milestones to measure project success.
âœ… Resource Planning â€“ Ensures teams are not overloaded and that resources are distributed efficiently.
âœ… Easy Adjustments â€“ Updates can be made to accommodate changes in deadlines or scope.
âœ… Progress Monitoring â€“ Tracks actual progress against the planned schedule.

ðŸ“Œ Example Use Case:
A software development project might use a Gantt chart to map out:

Week 1-2: Requirements gathering
Week 3-4: UI/UX design
Week 5-8: Development phase (frontend and backend)
Week 9-10: Testing and debugging
Week 11: Deployment and client review
ðŸš€ Popular Gantt Chart Tools: Microsoft Project, Trello, Asana, Monday.com, and Smartsheet.

